<HL>
   Finnish Inflation Eases
</HL>
<DATE>
04/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   HELSINKI -- Finland's inflation rate fell to 6.5% in March
from 7.4% in February and was down from 6.6% a year earlier,
the Central Statistical Office said.
   The principal reason for the easing in the consumer price
index was a slower rise in home prices, the statistical
office said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   House prices went up 10.7% in March, against more than 13%
earlier this year and in 1989, the office said.
</TEXT>
