<HL>
   Hong Kong's Jobless Rate
</HL>
<DATE>
04/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST
</CO>
<LP>
   HONG KONG -- Hong Kong's jobless rate for the three months
through February edged up to 1.5% from 1.2% a year earlier
and 1.3% in the preceding three months.
   The number of unemployed people was estimated at 17,500,
up slightly from 17,200 a year ago, but down from 22,000 in
the three months through November.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The underemployment rate in the latest period was 0.6%,
unchanged from a year earlier and off from 0.8% in the
preceding three months. Underemployed people are those who
work fewer than 35 hours a week and are available for more
work.
   The provisional unemployment rate for the first quarter
was 1.6%, and the provisional underemployment level was 0.7%.
</TEXT>
