<GV>
ENERGY DEPARTMENT (ERG)
</GV>
<LP>
   LEXINGTON, Mass. -- Raytheon Co. said a subsidiary has
been selected by the Department of Energy to provide support
services at the Nevada nuclear weapons test site and a
Pacific operations site.
   Raytheon and the DOE will negotiate a contract for support
services valued at up to $625 million over five years, with
the first-year increment estimated at about $115 million, the
company said.
